  "market_context": "XAUUSD on the 15-minute chart showing a bullish leg up with expansion, followed by a retracement lower into a prior fair value gap / point of interest around the 110.500–110.875 area before resuming higher.",
  "key_observation": "An ideal continuation requires a point of interest, a clean reach into it, a V-shaped recovery, and a swift closure through the down-close candles — forming a protected swing without taking out the previous high.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify the prior bullish expansion leg up and wait to classify the following move as retracement, reversal, or consolidation.",
    "Step 2: Observe price retracing lower into a fair value gap / point of interest on the 15-minute chart.",
    "Step 3: Confirm the next candle delivers a V-shaped recovery, closing back over the series of down-close candles (change in state of delivery).",
    "Step 4: Mark the resulting swing low as a protected low, since the CISD and fair value gap held.",
    "Step 5: Note that the previous high has not yet been taken out, leaving buyside liquidity above as a draw for further expansion.",
    "Step 6: Anticipate continuation higher; price retests and expands, validating the protected swing and ideal continuation signature."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price retested the area and expanded higher as anticipated, confirming the ideal continuation.",
  "lessons": "An ideal continuation combines a POI tap, V-shaped recovery, and swift closure through opposing candles to form a protected swing. When the prior high is still untaken, expect further expansion toward that buyside liquidity.",
